title:{"type":"field","size":[492,17],"pos":[10,22],"locked":1,"font":"menu","show":"invert","border":1,"align":"center","value":"What is a Transition?"}
button3:{"type":"button","size":[60,20],"pos":[78,312],"script":"whatisatransition.0","text":"Index","style":"rect"}
field1:{"type":"field","size":[248,192],"pos":[254,110],"locked":1,"border":0,"value":"When Decker moves between cards, it can use a \"transition effect\", or simply a \"transition\".\n\nBy animating movement between cards, transitions can help produce the illusion of the cards being located in space relative to one another, helping make decks more intuitive to navigate. They can also add creative visual flair!\n\nIn this deck we'll explore how transitions work, how to get more, and even how to write your own with a little bit of scripting!"}
